The discrimination of the ‘hands’ of'D is necessarily beset with diffi- culty. Grabe found that the MS. had been collated and corrected throughout by either the scribe or a contemporary diortlzota (Dl), to whom he attributes occasional marginal additions which have now dis- appeared. More frequently the corrections belong in his judgement to a later hand, which Tischendorf attributes to the eighth century (Da). To Da seems to be due the retracing of the letters which had been faded by age. Lastly, Grabe mentions a manus recentissima, which has been distinguished as Db.
